%% last updated 23rd June 2026
%% root bm
%% VARIATION C — function-per-node, grouped by EVENT CHANNEL (input pipeline).
%% Strategy: same explode-into-nodes fix as variant A, but the clustering axis is
%% the INPUT channel, not the responsibility. Each of the three conduit entry
%% points owns a vertical pipeline (mouse / key / lifecycle): its flat router plus
%% the handlers that trigger only on that channel. Cross-channel logic that BOTH a
%% mouse gesture and a keystroke reach (createDatabase) and the pure builders sit
%% in a shared lane. Reads as "what does each kind of input do" — a different
%% question than variant A's "what are the responsibilities". Same node set and
%% edges as A; only the subgraph membership differs, so the two can be compared
%% side by side to see which grouping a reader finds faster.

%% ── BlockManager class shell (public conduit surface) ────────────────────────
